Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 05 of Head MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Mass' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'I describe' radio button is enabled and preselected
And 'I know' radio button is enabled
And 'Localization' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis' tab is enabled

When I select 'Localization' tab
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled
And 'Median' checkbox is enabled

And 'Frontal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Temporal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Parietal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Occipital' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infratentorial' checkbox is enabled

And 'Falx' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tentorium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lamina cribrosa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Optic nerve sheath' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intrasellar' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior clinoid process' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sphenoid wing' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cerebellopontine angle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sulcus sigmoideus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Trigone of the lateral ventricle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Insular cistern' checkbox is enabled
And 'Foramen magnum' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'I know' radio button
Then 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown menu
Then 'Histology known' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Histology known' checkbox
Then 'Benign' radio button is enabled
And 'Malignant' radio button is enabled
